E. 138th Street, south side, at Exterior Street. The site in the foreground, is part of the area which the W.P.A. built up as a trailer ca p for the convention of the American Legion in 1937. The view is southwestward across Exterior Street and shows the N.Y.State Canal Terminal and bridges (left) spanning
the Harlem River.
